00:19:08.121 --> 00:19:09.540
In general, these
are going to be

00:19:09.540 --> 00:19:15.339
things that occur directly owned
by you or in your-- sometimes

00:19:15.339 --> 00:19:16.130
you may not own it.

00:19:16.130 --> 00:19:18.160
But if you have direct
control over it,

00:19:18.160 --> 00:19:19.850
especially like some
facilities where

00:19:19.850 --> 00:19:23.450
you have a long-term lease or
if you have a arrangement where

00:19:23.450 --> 00:19:26.130
you put down a long term
for hire with a carrier,

00:19:26.130 --> 00:19:29.065
they still might be scope
one even if you didn't do it.

00:19:29.065 --> 00:19:31.670
It's Based on what
you defined as

00:19:31.670 --> 00:19:34.100
your organizational boundary.

00:19:34.100 --> 00:19:36.620
So scope one and scope two
are things that you basically

00:19:36.620 --> 00:19:39.040
have to report, because
you directly admitted

00:19:39.040 --> 00:19:41.120
them or they have electricity.

00:19:41.120 --> 00:19:44.020
Scope three are
things that you might

00:19:44.020 --> 00:19:46.570
want to consider within your
carbon footprint boundary

00:19:46.570 --> 00:19:50.780
but aren't directly owned
or within your organization.

00:19:50.780 --> 00:19:53.710
AUDIENCE: Generally
emissions from the usage

00:19:53.710 --> 00:19:55.910
would not be
considered [INAUDIBLE]

00:19:55.910 --> 00:19:58.570
for the purpose of this?

00:19:58.570 --> 00:20:00.490
PROFESSOR: Of the
products that you produce?

00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:02.710
Yeah.

00:20:02.710 --> 00:20:07.262
Yes, so we'll talk about
this a little bit later.

00:20:07.262 --> 00:20:09.720
Scope three is anything that's
not scope one and scope two.

00:20:09.720 --> 00:20:14.615
And you may be
mandated on a minimum

00:20:14.615 --> 00:20:15.666
that you need to include.

00:20:15.666 --> 00:20:17.040
But usually there's
no regulation

00:20:17.040 --> 00:20:20.520
that says you can't include
something in your boundary.

00:20:20.520 --> 00:20:23.510
So you could include those
within your company's boundary.

00:20:23.510 --> 00:20:26.680
But if it's a product you're
selling to a consumer,

00:20:26.680 --> 00:20:30.690
that would fall under
scope three of indirect.

00:20:30.690 --> 00:20:32.530
And we'll talk a little
